      • getInetAddress

        public static java.net.InetAddress getInetAddress()
                                           throws java.io.IOException
        Returns network host in the following preferences order: (1)IPv4 host, (2)IPv6 host if IPv4 host is not found, (3)localhost if none of the above is found.

        The method InetAddress.getLocalHost() returns localhost on a Linux. Also, Linux returns IPv6 host _before_ IPv4 host while IPv4 return value is preferable in many cases. Thus more complex method to find a host is required.

        Returns:
        network address
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException
